Classification of ECG Waveform¶

By: Rohit Pardasani¶

About Data¶

  1. The PTB Diagnostic ECG Database Number of Samples: 14552
    Number of Categories: 2
    Sampling Frequency: 125Hz
    Data Source: Physionet's PTB Diagnostic Database
  2. All the samples are cropped, downsampled and padded with zeroes if necessary to the fixed dimension of 188.
  3. The Physikalisch-Technische Bundesanstalt (PTB) is the national metrology institute of the Federal Republic of Germany, with scientific and technical service tasks.https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physikalisch-Technische_Bundesanstalt
  4. Primary Source: https://physionet.org/content/ptbdb/1.0.0/ Paper: https://www.deepdyve.com/lp/de-gruyter/nutzung-der-ekg-signaldatenbank-cardiodat-der-ptb-ber-das-internet-uemKpjIFzM
  5. Secondary Source: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/shayanfazeli/heartbeat
  6. Two categories: Normal (4046) and Abnormal (12291) as picked from secondary source.
  7. For this AI-SIG session: Class balanced. Normal (4046) and Abnormal (4046)
  8. We have created a toy dataset

Let's first split the set into training, validation and test¶

  1. We will first shuffle both normal and abnormal samples dataframes
  2. Then we will pick 80% samples of each class for training and validation, keeping 20% for test
  3. Out of 80% of training and validation, we keep 80% of that i.e. 64% (0.8*0.8 = 0.64) of total for training and remaining 16% of total for validation
  4. Once we have training, validation and test set classwise, we merge them and create one training, one validation and one test set which contains equal samples of both classes

from tensorflow.keras.optimizers import SGD,Adam

Understand the model architecture by tracking how layers are being added¶

In [18]:
def get1DCNN(kSize = 7, TOTAL_PTS = 187, CHANNELS_INPUT = 1):
    seed(7)
    model = ks.Sequential()
    # Conv Layer 1
    model.add(Conv1D(filters=32, kernel_size=kSize, strides=1, input_shape=(TOTAL_PTS,CHANNELS_INPUT),padding='same'))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Activation('relu'))
    model.add(MaxPool1D(pool_size=5,padding='same'))
    
    #Conv Layer 2
    model.add(Conv1D(filters=64, kernel_size=kSize, strides=1,padding='same'))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Activation('relu'))
    model.add(MaxPool1D(pool_size=5,padding='same'))
    
    #Conv Layer 3
    model.add(Conv1D(filters=128, kernel_size=kSize, strides=1,padding='same'))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Activation('relu'))
    model.add(MaxPool1D(pool_size=5,padding='same'))
    
    #Conv Layer 4
    model.add(Conv1D(filters=256, kernel_size=kSize, strides=1,padding='same'))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Activation('relu'))
    model.add(MaxPool1D(pool_size=5,padding='same'))
    
    #Conv Layer 5
    model.add(Conv1D(filters=512, kernel_size=kSize, strides=1,padding='same'))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Activation('relu'))
    model.add(MaxPool1D(pool_size=5,padding='same'))
    
    # Flatten followed by 6 dense layers
    model.add(Flatten())
    model.add(Dense(512, activation='relu'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.5))
    model.add(Dense(256, activation='relu'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.5))
    model.add(Dense(128, activation='relu'))
    model.add(Dense(64, activation='relu'))
    model.add(Dense(32, activation='relu'))
    model.add(Dense(2, activation="softmax"))
    model.compile(optimizer="adam", loss="categorical_crossentropy",metrics=CategoricalAccuracy())
    return model

Function to create data to feed to model. Creating numpy arrays from dataframe. Notice that output is one-hot encoded.¶

In [20]:
from tensorflow.keras.utils import to_categorical
def createXY(df,onlyX=False,TOTAL_PTS=187,CHANNELS_INPUT=1,OUTPUT_DIM=2):
    N = len(df)
    X = np.zeros((N,TOTAL_PTS,CHANNELS_INPUT),dtype=np.float32)
    X[:,:,0] = df.iloc[:,0:TOTAL_PTS].values
    if not onlyX:
        Y = to_categorical(df['Class'].values)
        return X,Y
    else:
        return X

Function to train the model¶

In [22]:
def trainModel(X_TRAIN, Y_TRAIN, X_VALID, Y_VALID, model, modelName, EPOCHS = 40, BATCH_SIZE = 32):
    destPath = './' + modelName + '/'
    if not os.path.isdir(destPath):
        os.mkdir(destPath) 
    fpath = destPath + modelName
    csv_logger = CSVLogger(fpath+'.csv')
    model_checkpoint = ModelCheckpoint(fpath+'.h5', monitor='val_loss', verbose=1, save_best_only=True, 
                                       save_weights_only=False, mode='auto', period=1)
    results = model.fit(x=X_TRAIN, y=Y_TRAIN, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, epochs=EPOCHS, verbose=1,
             callbacks=[csv_logger,model_checkpoint], validation_data=(X_VALID, Y_VALID))
    print('Score on validation set')
    score = model.evaluate(X_VALID, Y_VALID, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE)
    print(score)
    return model,results,fpath

Plotting RoC for each of the set, calculating AUC and choosing best threshold¶

In [27]:
import sklearn.metrics
tvals_train = Y_TRAIN[:,1]
pvals_train = Y_TRAIN_predict[:,1]
tvals_valid = Y_VALID[:,1]
pvals_valid = Y_VALID_predict[:,1]
tvals_test = Y_TEST[:,1]
pvals_test = Y_TEST_predict[:,1]

fpr_train,tpr_train,thresholds_train = sklearn.metrics.roc_curve(tvals_train,pvals_train)
fpr_valid,tpr_valid,thresholds_valid = sklearn.metrics.roc_curve(tvals_valid,pvals_valid)
fpr_test,tpr_test,thresholds_test = sklearn.metrics.roc_curve(tvals_test,pvals_test)

ind_train = np.argmax(tpr_train-fpr_train)
thresh_train = thresholds_train[ind_train]
auc_train = sklearn.metrics.auc(fpr_train, tpr_train)

ind_valid = np.argmax(tpr_valid-fpr_valid)
thresh_valid = thresholds_valid[ind_valid]
auc_valid = sklearn.metrics.auc(fpr_valid, tpr_valid)

ind_test = np.argmax(tpr_test-fpr_test)
thresh_test = thresholds_test[ind_test]
auc_test = sklearn.metrics.auc(fpr_test, tpr_test)
            
plt.plot(fpr_train,tpr_train,label='Train'+' (AUC: '+str("%.3f" % round(auc_train, 3))+', '
         + 'Best Thresh: '+str("%.6f" % round(thresh_train, 6))+')')
plt.plot(fpr_valid,tpr_valid,label='Validation'+' (AUC: '+str("%.3f" % round(auc_valid, 3))+', '
         + 'Best Thresh: '+str("%.6f" % round(thresh_valid, 6))+')')
plt.plot(fpr_test,tpr_test,label='Test'+' (AUC: '+str("%.3f" % round(auc_test, 3))+', '
         + 'Best Thresh: '+str("%.6f" % round(thresh_test, 6))+')')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate (Sensitivity)')
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate (1 - Specificity)')
plt.legend()
plt.show()
